## Dependencies

- The real interface depends on the vendor-specific SDK or library
- Common patterns include `importlib` for Python SDKs and `ctypes` for C/C++ shared libraries

## Common Pitfalls

- Ensure the vendor SDK is installed and its path is accessible
- Some SDKs require specific Python versions or platform architectures
- Vendor SDKs may not be thread-safe; protect shared state with locks if needed
- Always call `disconnect()` to release SDK resources, even on errors
- Consider wrapping SDK calls in try/except to handle vendor-specific exceptions
